Some time ago we experienced a series of weird access violation exceptions in an ASP.NET web application running on .NET 4.7.2. We found a `NullReferenceException` in our code, and the fix made the problem disappear. 

After some investigation we were able to provide a [minimal demo](https://github.com/radischevo/RyuJitBugDemo) that can always be reproduced on .NET 4.7.2 and .NET Core 2.1.x (both Windows and MacOS) when built in Release configuration against x64. 

```
public static class Program
{
    public static void Main(string[] args)
    {
        Container container = null;
        Console.WriteLine($"{container.Item}.");
    }
}

public struct Option
{
    private object _foo;
    private int _bar;
}

public class Container
{
    public Option Item { get; }
}
```

